{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 09:50:54.650071", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and objective\\nAssess end-to-end host reachability and the health of the EBGP Clos fabric (super-spine, spines, leaves), detect anomalies, localize faulty elements, and identify root cause.\\n\\nSummary of findings\\n- Anomaly detected: End-to-end host connectivity is broken. pc_0_0 cannot reach pc_0_1, and pc_0_1 cannot reach pc_0_0.\\n- Fabric control plane health: All EBGP sessions between super-spine, spines, and leaves are established and exchanging the expected prefixes. Route propagation across the fabric is correct.\\n- Fault localization: The issue is localized to host pc_0_0. Its NIC eth0 is administratively/operationally down and it lacks any routing table entries, preventing any traffic transmission or reception.\\n- Root cause: Host interface down on pc_0_0 (eth0 state DOWN), resulting in no connected route and no default route on the host.\\n\\nEvidence and analysis\\n\\n1) Reachability tests\\n- pc_0_0 -> pc_0_1: ping returns “connect: Network is unreachable” (immediate local failure).\\n- pc_0_1 -> pc_0_0: ping attempt timed out (no response), consistent with destination host being offline/unreachable at L2/L3.\\n\\n2) Host interface and routing state\\n- pc_0_0:\\n  - IP config: inet 10.0.0.2/24 on eth0.\\n  - Interface state: eth0 is DOWN (ip addr shows state DOWN; ifconfig flags lack UP).\\n  - Routing table: empty (no connected 10.0.0.0/24 route, no default route).\\n  - Conclusion: The host cannot send any packets; kernel immediately reports “Network is unreachable.”\\n- pc_0_1:\\n  - IP config: inet 10.0.1.2/24 on eth0; interface state UP/LOWER_UP.\\n  - Routing: default via 10.0.1.1, connected 10.0.1.0/24 present.\\n  - Conclusion: This host is correctly configured and ready to forward via its leaf.\\n\\n3) Fabric routing (FRR EBGP) – control-plane\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200):\\n  - Connected: 10.0.0.0/24 on eth2.\\n  - BGP-learned: 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.4 (to spine 0_0).\\n  - BGP summary: 2 peers (both spines) established; prefixes received = 1 (the remote leaf’s /24).\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201):\\n  - Connected: 10.0.1.0/24 on eth2.\\n  - BGP-learned: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (to spine 0_0).\\n  - BGP summary: 2 peers established; prefixes received = 1 (the other leaf’s /24).\\n- spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100):\\n  - BGP-learned: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.5 (leaf 0_0), 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.7 (leaf 0_1).\\n  - BGP summary: Peers with super-spine and both leaves; established; receiving expected prefixes from leaves.\\n- spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101):\\n  - BGP-learned: 10.0.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.9 (leaf 0_0), 10.0.1.0/24 via 172.16.0.11 (leaf 0_1).\\n  - BGP summary: Peers with super-spine and both leaves; established; receiving expected prefixes from leaves.\\n- super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000):\\n  - BGP-learned: both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 received from spines; selected next-hop via 172.16.0.1 (one spine).\\n  - BGP summary: 2 peers (both spines) established; prefixes received = 2 (both leaf /24s).\\n- Conclusion: EBGP peering is up across the fabric; route exchange aligns with the Clos design; both leaf /24 networks are present in the fabric.\\n\\n4) Data-plane implications\\n- With pc_0_0’s NIC down, there can be no ARP resolution or L2/L3 forwarding to/from 10.0.0.2. Even though the fabric has correct routes, the endpoint is offline at L2, causing end-to-end failure.\\n\\nDiagnosis\\n- Primary anomaly: Host-to-host connectivity failure.\\n- Localized faulty device: pc_0_0.\\n- Root cause: pc_0_0 eth0 interface is down, which removes its connected route and any default route, leading to immediate “Network is unreachable” on transmit and no responses to inbound probes.\\n\\nNetwork health assessment\\n- Fabric control-plane: Healthy (all BGP sessions established; expected prefixes present).\\n- Fabric forwarding: Likely healthy; no evidence of routing anomalies in the fabric.\\n- Endpoint layer: Unhealthy at pc_0_0 due to downed NIC, causing the observed reachability issue., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='6ee751ce-f8f7-4a28-aefd-0f48723a0716'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
